sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device expresses RFP,YFP,CFP respectively under different oxygen concentration. RFP is expressed under anaerobic conditions. YFP is expressed under microaerobic conditions. CFP is expressed under aerobic conditions and is repressed with the existence of TetR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: MA Keyue
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: vgb promoter comes from Vitreoscilla sp. and fdhF comes from E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We construct tetR to resist CFP expression under microaerobic and anaerobic conditions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The expression of YFP and tetR is under the control of microaerobic promoter vgb. The expression of tetR will repress Ptet.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: HUA Yijie, PI Ruoxi, XIA Yu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: vgb promoter comes from Vitreoscilla sp.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Because vgb promoter induces high expression under microaerobic conditions and induces lower expression under anaerobic conditions, we used medium RBS to resist it from inducing expression under anaerobic conditions.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K561002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The expression of RFP and tetR is under the control of anaerobic promoter fdhF. The expression of tetR will repress Ptet.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: XU Chenlin, PI Ruoxi, HUA Yijie, MA Lie
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: fdhF comes from E.coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This device has strong RBS.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ecfp
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part accepts POPS to generate EYFP under the medium strength RBS B0032.

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999)

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
